						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Saṁkama, 1180 A.D. </p>						

						<p>This is dated the 5th regnal year of the king, Śārvari, Chaitra śu. 11, Sunday, corresponding to 1180 A.D., March 9.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of money to the god Asitara Kēśavāditya.</p>						

